title: No. 3 Utah loses starting TE Fakailoatonga for the season
text:
No. 3 Utah loses starting TE Fakailoatonga for the season Associated Press 3 hrs ago Â© Russ Isabella-USA TODAY Sports Utah Utes tight end Siale Fakailoatonga catches a pass from quarterback Kendal Thompson (not pictured) during the first half against the Utah State Aggies at Rice-Eccles Stadium in Salt Lake City. Utah won 24-14. SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Utah starting tight end Siale Fakailoatonga is out for the season after being injured in the 34-18 win against Arizona State on Saturday.
AdChoices Coach Kyle Whittingham made the announcement Monday but did not elaborate on the injury.
The third-ranked Utes (6-0), the last undefeated team in the Pac-12, play at USC on Saturday.
Fakailoatonga started the last five games after Evan Moeai was lost for season in the opener. He had 12 receptions for 120 yards, ranking fourth on the team in both categories.
Sophomore Harrison Handley moves to the top of the depth chart and freshman Caleb Repp is listed as the backup. Handley has two touchdowns on nine receptions this season.
